This option allows you to query and set the DB session ID by running separate SQL in the DB to query the DB session ID.

The setting is made by concatenating the SQL that queries the class and DB session ID that are used when connecting the actual Connection object using a colon (:).

The following is an example configuration for Oracle DB.

    oracle:select SYS_CONTEXT ('USERENV','SESSIONID') sid from dual

Note that the DB session ID tracking function works only when the Connection object is traceable.

---

* Default : None
* Format : String (DB:SQL)
* Restart : Not Required
